Verify the wire connections are correct on the garage door opener.";i:10;s:113:"The solid white wires connect insert to the white terminal and the whiteblack wires connect to the grey terminal.";i:11;s:85:"The amber LED on the sending sensor will glow regardless of alignment or obstruction.";i:12;s:66:"If the green LED on the receiving sensor is off dim or flickering.";i:13;s:93:"The garage door sensor yellow light and the green light together create a solid illumination.";i:14;s:138:"If you do not see a solid illumination or your garage door is not working the problem is most likely due to the sensors being out of line.";i:15;s:29:"So how do you fix this issue.";i:16;s:81:"Youll need to first equip yourself with a wrench of some sort and a tape measure.";i:17;s:26:"Once you have these tools.";i:18;s:30:"Start by measuring one of the.";i:19;s:72:"When you inspect your garage door sensors youll notice each has a light.";i:20;s:39:"This light will either be red or green.";i:21;s:79:"The light of both sensors should be green if the unit is functioning correctly.";i:22;s:89:"This confirms that the beam of infrared light is being produced and read by both sensors.";i:23;s:93:"Slowly rotate sensor back aligning sensor with sending sensor until it lights up green again.";i:24;s:93:"When you have a strong green light put it back into the bracket and put the wing nut back on.";i:25;s:191:"If you are unable to get the door closed and the safety sensors are the issue the garage door can be closed by pressing and holding the push button on the wall until down travel is completed.";i:26;s:54:"Sensor power Reconnect the sensor to its power supply.";i:27;s:78:"A common cause of a malfunctioning garage door sensor is lack of power supply.";i:28;s:41:"Look for small LED lights on the sensors.";i:29;s:85:"If theyre turned on in both the sensors then there is no issue with the power supply.";i:30;s:128:"If your LiftMaster garage door light wont turn off or on there is likely a problem with your doors motion sensor or light timer.";i:31;s:104:"More specifically if your garage door light wont shut off it is most likely due to one of these reasons.";i:32;s:100:"Something is triggering your garage door motion sensors which are responsible for turning the light.";i:33;s:148:"When your garage door does not close and the garage door opener lights flash 10 times there are a few simple steps required to figure out the issue.";i:34;s:131:"The safety reversing sensors must be connected and aligned correctly before the garage door opener will move in the down direction.";i:35;s:113:"Today were going to talk about troubleshooting a garage door opener that wont close the door and blinks 10 times.";i:36;s:99:"The blinking opener lights indicate that the safety sensors are likely blocked or out of alignment.";i:37;s:42:"Defective safety sensors or faulty sensor.";i:38;s:108:"Genie garage door openers use a green light for the sending sensor and a red light for the receiving sensor.";i:39;s:83:"When Genie safety sensors are misaligned the red receiving sensor light will blink.";i:40;s:148:"This is a nice feature because if the light is blinking then you know you have power going to the receiving sensor all you have to do is align them.";i:41;s:59:"Get shopping advice from experts friends and the community.";i:42;s:63:"I have a 12 hp craftsman garage door opener model 13953975srt1.";i:43;s:83:"It does not respond to the remote or it may move the door six inches and then stop.";i:44;s:152:"The sending unit is glowing yellow as indicated in the manual but the receiving sensor LED does not glow even when I hold the lenses against each other.";i:45;s:127:"Johnson invented the first electric garage door opener in 1926 in Hartford Indiana it mustve seemed like a little bit of magic.";i:46;s:203:"But electric garage door openers only became popular after World War II when the Era Meter Company of Chicago invented a garage door opener activated by a switch inside the garage or a key panel outside.";i:47;s:45:"Years later of course the ability to open or.";i:48;s:152:"An easy way to tell if your garage door sensors are out of alignment is by checking if the exterior LED light blinks when you attempt to close the door.";i:49;s:96:"Green lights mean the sensors are working while red lights indicate the sensors are not aligned.";i:50;s:74:"If you see red lights try inspecting the bracket or tightening a screw on.";i:51;s:70:"Look for an error code from the blinking LED light on your motor unit.";i:52;s:61:"For a Liftmaster Chamberlain or Craftsman garage door opener.";i:53;s:42:"If it is a single LED light it will flash.";i:54;s:45:"1 blink if the sensor wires are disconnected.";i:55;s:34:"2 blinks if the sensor wires have.";}}